    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2009-02-03</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2009-04-20T18:21:19Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Mercury Emissions Reduction Act - Declares that this Act's purpose is to require the Administrator of the Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) to promulgate a rule that requires mercury emissions from electric utility steam generating units to be subject to Maximum Achievable Control Technology (MACT) standards under the Clean Air Act for hazardous air pollutants.</p> <p>Amends the Clean Air Act to require the Administrator to promulgate standards for mercury emissions from electric utility steam generating units.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
